Steven F. Leer: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 21, 2017 1:34 PM ET
Building Products

Company Overview of USG Corporation



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Steven F. Leer  Non-Executive Chairman, USG CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 7 Board Members in 7 different organizations across 9 different industries.See Board Relationships64$230,050
Background

		Mr. Steven F. Leer, also known as Steve, has been Non-Executive Chairman of USG Corporation since November 1, 2016 and served as its Lead Director since January 1, 2012. Mr. Leer has been Lead Independent Director at Norfolk Southern Corporation since May 09, 2013 and has been its Independent Director since 1999. Mr. Leer has been an Independent Director of Cenovus Energy Inc. since April 29, 2015. He serves as Independent Director of Parsons Corporation. He has been ... an Independent Director of Norfolk Southern Corp. and Southern Railway Co. Mobile & Ohio RR Co. since 1999. He has been a Director of USG Corporation since June 2005. He serves on the boards of the BRT and the University of the Pacific. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Arch Coal Inc. from 1992 to April 26, 2012 and served as its President from 1992 to April 28, 2006. He served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Arch Mineral Corporation, one of Arch Coal's predecessor companies. He also held senior management positions with The Valvoline Company, a subsidiary of Ashland Inc. He served as an Executive Chairman of Arch Coal Inc. from April 28, 2006 to April 24, 2014 and served as its Executive Director from 1992 to April 24, 2014. He served as a Director of GP Natural Resource Partners LLC, the General Partner of Natural Resource Partners LP since April 2002. He serves as District Chairman of the New Horizons District, Greater St. Louis Area Council of the Boy Scouts of America. He served as the Chairman of Center for Energy and Economic Development, the National Coal Council and the National Mining Association. He serves on the boards of the Western Business Roundtable and the Mineral Information Institute. He serves as a Director at the Greater St. Louis Area Boy Scouts of America. Mr. Leer serves as a Trustee of Washington University, St. Louis. He serves on the boards of the Center for Energy and Economic Development, the National Coal Council and the National Mining Association. He is a member of The Business Roundtable and the National Association of Manufacturers. In addition, he is a delegate to the Coal Industry Advisory Board of the International Energy Agency in Paris. Mr. Leer holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Electrical Engineering from the University of the Pacific and an MBA from Washington University's Olin School of Business. Mr. Leer was awarded an honorary doctorate by University of the Pacific in May 1993.Read Full Background




